  "narrative": "3.125(a) \n   \nFacilities, general. \nAn outdoor enclosure housing seventy-five goats was not being maintained properly and had several exposed nails and \nscrews within reach of the animals. The elevated walking platforms had screws exposed on the walking surface. The \nelevated shelter had several screws exposed with some having goat hair around the screws. The enclosure fence had a \nboard that had fallen to the ground with several screws with sharp points that could contact the animals. There is a \npotential source of injury to the enclosed animals. The sharp points and screws need to be removed or secured. All \nhousing facilities shall be structurally sound and shall be maintained in good repair to protect the animals from injury.  \nCorrected at time of inspection. \n \nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with a facility representative. \n \n n",
